⸻

ArrayList

List<String> customers =
        new ArrayList<>();
customers.add("John");
customers.add("Mary");

Characteristics

* Ordered
* Allows duplicates
* Fast reads
* Slower insertions in middle

Time Complexity

Operation	Complexity
get()	O(1)
add()	O(1)
insert middle	O(n)
remove middle	O(n)

⸻

LinkedList

List<String> customers =
        new LinkedList<>();

Characteristics

* Fast insertions
* Slow random access
* Doubly-linked list

Time Complexity

Operation	Complexity
get()	O(n)
insert	O(1)
delete	O(1)

⸻

HashSet

Set<String> customers =
        new HashSet<>();
customers.add("John");
customers.add("John");

Output:

[John]

Characteristics

* No duplicates
* Unordered
* Fast lookup

⸻

HashMap

Map<Long, Customer> customers =
        new HashMap<>();
customers.put(1L, customer);

Characteristics

* Key-value structure
* Allows one null key
* Not thread-safe
* O(1) average lookup

⸻

ConcurrentHashMap

Map<Long, Customer> cache =
        new ConcurrentHashMap<>();

Characteristics

* Thread-safe
* Supports concurrent access
* Preferred in multi-threaded systems

